      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics assumptions (linear elastic, small deformation, isotropic Ti-6Al-4V) justified against test regime; contact formulation validated against published literature. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct tested below yield in stiffness regime; linear elastic isotropic material appropriate for Ti-6Al-4V implant components. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) between screw and rod validated against two published F1717 studies showing less than 5% QoI sensitivity to friction coefficient in 0.1–0.3 range. Model form adequate for intended QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from ASTM-certified coupon testing of same material lot; geometric inputs from CMM measurements of test articles. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa) and yield strength (880 MPa) from tensile coupon testing of Ti-6Al-4V bar stock from same material lot as test constructs. Screw and rod geometry from CMM measurements of three production samples; dimensional variation below 0.05 mm. Screening sensitivity study identified elastic modulus as the dominant input parameter; uncertainty bounded by coupon test variability (CV 1.2%)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs assembled from production-representative components; sample traceability documented. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "N=11 constructs assembled from production-representative 7.5 mm non-cannulated pedicle screws and 5.5 mm rods. Component lot numbers and assembly records archived. Statistical power adequate for detecting 10% QoI difference at 80% power."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two load levels or two boundary condition configurations representative of clinical loading envelope. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at single load configuration per ASTM F1717 protocol (compression-bending, 10 mm offset). Only one test condition evaluated; clinical loading envelope includes additional modes (torsion, lateral bending) not assessed here. Achieved level 2; this factor is below required level and represents a known gap accepted by the credibility team given the regulatory context of a standard-compliant submission."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions) verified to match experimental test article parameters within measurement uncertainty. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "FEA geometry derived from CMM measurements of actual test articles. Boundary conditions replicate F1717 fixture: fixed inferior block, superior block free to translate axially, 10 mm anterior offset. Grip stiffness verified against fixture compliance measurement. Input equivalency confirmed by pre-test FEA prediction within 3% of subsequent experimental mean."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric; acceptance threshold E/uval < 1.96 for all primary QoIs. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "E/uval computed for stiffness (0.81), yield force (1.44), and force at 40 mm (1.12). All three QoIs pass the pre-established acceptance threshold of 1.96. Percentage differences 4.2%, 7.6%, and 5.9% respectively, all below 10% bound. Output comparison fully satisfactory."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
