      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements. Required level 3.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness relates to load sharing with bone graft; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are the primary regulatory endpoints for F1717 submissions. QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision on construct mechanical adequacy."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
